postcode_sector: For population: 'In order to protect against disclosure of personal information, records have been swapped between different geographic areas. Some counts will be affected, particularly small counts at the lowest geographies.' (ONS)
Numpeople_2011_Total is total postcode sector population, calculated by summing all postcodes within. Numpeople_2011_Wales is population for all Welsh postcodes within the sector.
Both SFP and RDP use CaseID2 as identifier.
Where there are multiple counties, their order does not necessarily reflect their size relative to the postcode sector.

For postcodes on the border, I'm not sure exactly what the criteria is for them to be classified as English or Welsh. I can't find an answer online, though I assume it is because of geography rather than population because some Welsh postcodes have no population (see CH1 4). In any case, I don't think it's an issue.
County' is the local authority district. 'CountyCe' is the ceremonial county.
